Class AbstractFileSystem

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gxp.compiler.fs.AbstractFileSystem
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
DummyFileSystem, InMemoryFileSystem, ResourceFileSystem, SystemFileSystem
public abstract class AbstractFileSystem
extends Object
implements FileSystem

Abstract base class for typical implementations of FileSystem. This is useful for implementing FileSystems that have all of the following characteristics:

  • use a single FileStore
  • represent a filename list as a sequence of filenames separated by some delimiter which can be matched by a regular expression

getRoot

public final FileRef getRoot()
Returns a FileRef for the root of this FileSystem. The the abstract name of the root is always "/".

This implementation simply returns a FileRef with the abstract name "/" on the FileStore returned by getFileStore().

Specified by:
getRoot in interface FileSystem

parseFilenameList

public final List<FileRef> parseFilenameList(String filenameList)
Parses a system path in this filesystem into an list of abstract FileRef objects. A "system path" is a string that specifies a list of filenames. These are typically used for search paths, eg: class path, library path, command path, etc. They are usually represented by some number of system filenames separated by a system-specific delimiter, but the actual representation is implementation specific.

This implementation splits filenameList using the result of getFilenameListDelimiter() and parses the resulting filenames with FileSystem.parseFilename(String).

Specified by:
parseFilenameList in interface FileSystem
Returns:
an Unmodifiable List of FileRefs
